Efficient User Management: Google Vault Actions to Set up Users on Hold #
GAT Flow is a user management tool that empowers Google Admins within the domain to ef ficiently handle tasks such as onboarding, of fboarding, and user
modifications.
The admins can set up many automated actions to be taken on one or bulk users at once.
One of the actions that can be taken for this can be found at: Vault.google.com
1. Select action #
This action can be set up in normal workflow , event, or recurring workflow .
Create the workflow you want.  In choosing actions click on the button to add action.
The Actions available actions will be displayed.
Search and select Set Google Vault hold

Effortless User Management:  How to Remove Users from Google Vault Holds #
GAT Flow  allows you to manage your domain users conveniently by setting up the workflows that will trigger mass actions.
One of them is to remove your users from the Google Vault hold  set up earlier .
You can delete the users’  holds by following the steps outlined below .
Select action #
The action Remove user  from hold  can be performed either on a one-of f regular workflow ( Create workflow ),  Even workflow , or Recurring workflow .
To create a workflow that removes user(s) from Google Vault hold, add the relevant action into it by clicking on the ‘Add action’  + button (left side of the graph).
The available actions will be displayed by default.
Search and select Remove user  from hold  action.

A Step-by-Step Guide to Creating a Google Vault Export #
GAT Flow  helps Google Workspace  Admins  with many tasks and responsibilities as it is an ‘ all in one  solution for managing the Google Workspace domain. The
admins can set up many automated actions to be taken on one or bulk users at once.
GAT Flow  allows managing Google Vault users with the below actions:
1. Setting Google Vault users on hold
2. Removing users from Google Vault hold 
3. Creating Google Vault export
In this post, we’ll outline the process of creating a Google Vault export.
1. Select action #
The action  Create Google Vault export  can be performed either on a one-of f regular workflow ( Create workflow ),  Even workflow , or Recurring workflow .
To create a workflow that creates user(s) Google Vault export, add the relevant action into it by clicking on the ‘Add action’  + button (left side of the graph).
The available actions will be displayed by default.
Search and select  Remove user  from hold  action.

metadata.file_name: STREAMLINING GOOGLE VAULT EXPORTS WITH GAT FLOW.pdf
STREAMLINING GOOGLE VAULT EXPORTS WITH GAT FLOW.pdf

__data__.text:
9/22/23, 10:55 PM about:blank
about:blank 2/5
When the action is selected fill in the required details.
1. Matter  – Select the name of the existing Google Vault Matter that the export will refer to;
2. Export name – Type the name of this export that will be displayed in Google Vault under the particular Matter ’s export tab;
3. Service – Choose the relevant service from the pop-up list:
1. Drive
2. Mail
3. Hangout chat
4. Data scope
1. All data
2. Held data
3. Unpr ocessed data
5. Time zone – Select the time zone
6. Date range – Select the particular date range to explicitly export only data from that period;
7. Terms – Enter a particular term for exporting data;
8. Depending on the Service type selected:
1. If Drive  service is selected, the option to Include shar ed drives  can be toggled
2. If Mail  service is selected, the option to Exclude email drafts  can be toggled
3. If the Hangout chat  service is selected, the option to Include messages fr om the chat space  can be toggled
9. When the workflow is ready click on Send appr oval r equest .

In Google Vault navigate to the Matters (2), select the relevant Matter from the list of existing ones (2), and go to the Exports tab (3). The Export Status, Name, Days

Hovering your mouse over the right side of the area reveals the Download or Delete Export option.
